# Trivy vulnerability-ID suppressions for CI filesystem scans.
#
# Scope: this file is consumed by the `.github/workflows/security.yml`
# `trivy-fs` job. It accepts vulnerability identifiers (CVE, GHSA, DLA,
# KHV, AVD) — **one per line**. Path-based exclusions live in the action's
# `skip-dirs` input, not here (see security.yml).
#
# Maintenance policy:
#   * Every suppression must cite (a) the finding URL, (b) WHY we are not
#     exposed (unreachable code path / compile-time only / runtime mitigated),
#     and (c) an upstream tracking issue. An entry without justification is
#     grounds for rejecting the PR that adds it.
#   * Entries expire when the advisory database resolves them or the
#     dependency is upgraded; run `cargo audit` / scan output quarterly and
#     prune stale lines.
#
# (Empty list — no active Trivy suppressions at the moment. Cargo and pnpm
# advisories are handled by their dedicated scanners; see `backend/.cargo/audit.toml`.)
